<p>HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL 
Second session 
Agenda item 2 
</p>
<p><b>IMPLEMENTATION OF GENERAL ASSEMBLY RESOLUT</b>I<b>ON 60/251 
OF 15 MARCH 2006 ENTITLED &#8220;HUMAN RIGHTS COUNCIL&#8221; 
</b></p>
<p><b>Conclusion of the draft International Convention on the Rights of Persons  
with Disabilities and its Optional Protocol:  draft President&#8217;s statement 
</b></p>
<p> <i>The Human Rights Council</i>, 
</p>
<p> 1. <i>Welcomes</i> the conclusion of the draft text of the International Convention on the 
Rights of Persons with Disabilities and its Optional Protocol and their adoption by the Ad Hoc 
Committee on a Comprehensive and Integral International Convention on the Protection and 
Promotion of the Rights and Dignity of Persons with Disabilities, on 25 August 2006; 
</p>
<p> 2. <i>Looks forward</i> to the adoption of the draft Convention and Optional Protocol by 
the General Assembly during its sixty-first session and encourages the ongoing efforts by 
Member States in this regard; 
</p>
<p> 3. <i>Encourages</i> the international community to promote the entry into force of the 
Convention at the earliest possible stage. 
</p>
<p>----- 
</p>
